I went to see Oppenheimer over Barbie and I think frankly  the story of Oppenheimer and the way it is told is much more important to hear than Barbie.
The movie takes the opposite approach to modern filmmaking  it is a biography after all  and the subject matter is just so dark and impactful
There are parts of the movie where Nolan can make you physically jolt from shock of the sound in the theatre  and the emotion of seeing some of the choices they make is intense man

The intensity is driven not by just noise but the contrast of silence and appearance. It‚Äôs beautiful  not the most happy  but it tries to be true in telling the history of one of the most important things that happened in the last. It made me think quite a bit anyway  about something that remains relevant and true  about choices we make. Important movie for sure.

or is still happening to me

ok so when we were done with our 2nd call i went to buy lunch  my snr medic haven't even ordered his yet  then abt 1min before my food was ready  the snr medic told me that we got call and i have to go back to ambulance to go to call location
but then guess what  the paramedic told me to collect my food and go back to firepost
plot twist  firepost was locked  and i didn't have the key
so i was stuck outside in the hot sun (which was everyday in SAF so im used to it) for abt an hr  or maybe less
the other ambulance crew came back and then saw me outside and they were in shock
and i told them the situation of what happened  and i went inside
the other ambulance crew A122 (im A123) abt 10min later went for call
no lah dei i paid for it alr
and then i went to sleep (got nothing better to do)
then all of a sudden A123 got call  i woke up and saw the FP void of people
i checked outside to see if A123 was outside but it wasn't  so i realised they didn't even return to base and they got called
AND THE STORY DOESN'T END THERE

30min later  i see my snr medic call me like 2 times to ask me to collect his food  but me being the idiot i am went outside and closed the door  only to realise i didn't have key and the door auto locks
so once i went out and took the food and returned
when i went to SGH to send patient  A122 sent another patient at ard same time  turns out he was a cbt medic
